# Charge un fichier Excel  partir d'internet avec copyfileobj
def load_with_copyfileobj(file):  
    url = 'https://www.vendeeglobe.org/download-race-data/' + file
    with request.urlopen(url) as response, open(file, 'wb') as out_file:
        copyfileobj(response, out_file)
    return

# Lecture/criture d'un fichier Excel avec xlwings
def save_with_xlwings(file):
    tempfile = f'./xlwing_{file}'
    excel_app = xw.App(visible=False)
    excel_book = excel_app.books.open(file)
    excel_book.save(tempfile)
    excel_book.close()
    excel_app.quit()
    return tempfile

# liste de crneaux horraires pour importer les clasements
def create_list_dates():
     
    l_dates = []
    
    #crneaux du 8 novembre 2020 - Crer la liste des dates heures du 8 novembre 2020
    for hour in ['120200', '140000', '150000', '170000', '210000']:
        l_dates.append('20201108' + '_' + hour)

    #Crneaux du 9 novembre 2020 (inclus) au 27 janvier 2021 (inclu) - completer la liste des dates heures
    dates = list(pd.date_range(start='11/09/2020', end='01/27/2021').strftime('%Y%m%d'))
    for date in dates:
        for hour in ['040000','080000', '110000', '140000', '170000', '210000']:
            l_dates.append(date + '_' + hour)
            
    return l_dates
    

# Telecharge tous les fichiers de classement sous format excel de du 08 novembre 2020 au 27 janvier 2021
def download_ranking_files():
    # liste des crneaux horraires
    list_of_dates = create_list_dates()

    for date_hour in list_of_dates:
        xls_file = 'vendeeglobe_' + date_hour + '.xlsx'
        load_with_copyfileobj(xls_file)
        save_with_xlwings(xls_file)


# Charge les fichiers dans un dataframe 
def create_df_ranking():
    print("Creating df_ranking...")
    
    list_of_dates = create_list_dates()
    dfs = [(pd.read_excel(f"xlwing_vendeeglobe_{date_hour}.xlsx", index_col=None, header=None, skiprows=5, skipfooter=4,
                      names=["rank", "nat_sail", "skipper_crew", "hour_FR", "latitude", "longitude",
                            "heading_since_30mn", "speed_since_30mn", "VMG_since_30mn", "distance_since_30mn",
                            "heading_since_last", "speed_since_last", "VMG_since_last", "distance_since_last",
                            "heading_since_24hr", "speed_since_24hr", "VMG_since_24hr", "distance_since_24hr",
                            "DTF", "DTL"]).assign(date_hours=date_hour))
           for date_hour in list_of_dates]

    df = (pd.concat(dfs, ignore_index=True).loc[:, ["rank", "nat_sail", "skipper_crew", "hour_FR", "latitude", "longitude",
                            "heading_since_30mn", "speed_since_30mn", "VMG_since_30mn", "distance_since_30mn",
                            "heading_since_last", "speed_since_last", "VMG_since_last", "distance_since_last",
                            "heading_since_24hr", "speed_since_24hr", "VMG_since_24hr", "distance_since_24hr",
                            "DTF", "DTL", "date_hours"]])
    print("Done")
    return df


def create_df_boats_features():
    print("Creating df_boats_features...")
    # Retrouve l'ensemble des caractristiques sur les beateaux.
    page = requests.get("https://www.vendeeglobe.org/fr/glossaire")
    soup = BeautifulSoup(page.text, "lxml")
    list_tag_boats_specs = soup.find_all("ul", class_="boats-list__popup-specs-list")

    # Cre un dataframe avec l'information sur chaque bateau.
    list_dict_boat_specs = []

    for spec in list_tag_boats_specs:
        list_text_boat_specs = spec.text.split("\n")
        dict_boat_specs = {unidecode.unidecode(e.split(" : ")[0].lower().replace(" ", "_").replace("'", "_").replace("(", "").replace(")", "")) : e.split(" : ")[1] for e in list_text_boat_specs if " : " in e}
        list_dict_boat_specs.append(dict_boat_specs)

    df = pd.DataFrame.from_records(list_dict_boat_specs)
    print("Done")
    return df

# Adapt de https://stackoverflow.com/questions/50193159/converting-pandas-data-frame-with-degree-minute-second-dms-coordinates-to-deci
def dms2dd(s):
    # example: s = """051'56.29"S"""
    # exemple: s = 4624.46'N
    if  isinstance(s, str):
        degrees, minutes, direction = re.split("[\']+", s)
        dd = float(degrees) + float(minutes)/60;
        if direction in ('S','W'):
            dd*= -1
        return dd

def clean_df_ranking(df):
    print("Cleaning df_ranking...")
    res = df.copy()
    
    # Enlever les lignes inutiles.
    res = res.dropna(subset='rank')
    cond1 = res['rank'] != "RET"
    cond2 = res['date_hours'] != "20210127_170000"
    cond3 = res['date_hours'] != "20210127_210000"
    res = res.loc[cond1 & cond2 & cond3, :]
    res = res.dropna()

    # Nettoyer les colonnes.
    res["rank"] =  res["rank"].astype(int)
    res["nat_sail"] = res["nat_sail"].str[1:].str.replace(" |R\n", "", regex=True)
    res["skipper"] = res["skipper_crew"].apply(lambda x: str(x.split('\n')[0])).astype(str)
    res["crew"] = res["skipper_crew"].apply(lambda x: str(x.split('\n')[1])).astype(str)
    res["hour_FR"] = res["hour_FR"].str[:5]
    
    res["speed_since_30mn"] = res["speed_since_30mn"].apply(lambda x: str(x.split(' ')[0])).astype(float)
    res["VMG_since_30mn"] = res["VMG_since_30mn"].apply(lambda x: str(x.split(' ')[0])).astype(float)
    res["distance_since_30mn"] = res["distance_since_30mn"].apply(lambda x: str(x.split(' ')[0])).astype(float)

    res["speed_since_last"] = res["speed_since_last"].apply(lambda x: str(x.split(' ')[0])).astype(float)
    res["VMG_since_last"] = res["VMG_since_last"].apply(lambda x: str(x.split(' ')[0])).astype(float)
    res["distance_since_last"] = res["distance_since_last"].apply(lambda x: str(x.split(' ')[0])).astype(float)

    res["speed_since_24hr"] = res["speed_since_24hr"].apply(lambda x: str(x.split(' ')[0])).astype(float)
    res["VMG_since_24hr"] = res["VMG_since_24hr"].apply(lambda x: str(x.split(' ')[0])).astype(float)
    res["distance_since_24hr"] = res["distance_since_24hr"].apply(lambda x: str(x.split(' ')[0])).astype(float)
    
    res["DTF"] = res["DTF"].apply(lambda x: str(x.split(' ')[0])).astype(float)
    res["DTL"] = res["DTL"].apply(lambda x: str(x.split(' ')[0])).astype(float)
    
    res['longitude'] = res['longitude'].apply(dms2dd).astype(float)
    res['latitude'] = res['latitude'].apply(dms2dd).astype(float)
    
    res['heading_since_30mn'] = res["heading_since_30mn"].str.replace("", "").astype(int)
    res['heading_since_last'] = res["heading_since_last"].str.replace("", "").astype(int)
    res['heading_since_24hr'] = res["heading_since_24hr"].str.replace("", "").astype(int)
    
    res['date'] = pd.to_datetime(res.date_hours.str.split('_').str[0], format='%Y%m%d')

    # Cration de variables.
    res[["hour", "minute"]] = res.hour_FR.str.split(":", expand=True).astype(int)
    res["country"] = res.nat_sail.str[0:3]
 
    print("Done.")
    
    return res


def clean_df_boats_features(df):
    print("Cleaning df_boats_features...")
    res = df.copy()
    
    # Nettoie les colonnes du dataframe.
    res = res.dropna(subset = ['architecte'])  # bateau de Francois Guiffant sans info
    res.numero_de_voile = res.numero_de_voile.fillna("FRA59")  # le bateau FRA59 etait manquant
    res.numero_de_voile = res.numero_de_voile.str.replace(" ", "")
    res.longueur = res.longueur.str[0:5].str.replace(',', '.').astype(float)
    res.largeur = res.largeur.str[0:4].str.replace(',', '.').astype(float)
    res.tirant_d_eau = res.tirant_d_eau.str[0:4].str.replace(',', '.').astype(float)
    res.deplacement_poids = res.deplacement_poids.str.replace("NC|nc|tonnes|t", "", regex=True).str.replace(",", ".").replace("", np.nan).astype(float)
    res.loc[res.numero_de_voile == 'SUI07', "deplacement_poids"] = 9
    res.loc[res.numero_de_voile == 'FRA85', "deplacement_poids"] = 7.5
    res['presence_foil'] = res.nombre_de_derives.str.replace("foiler|foils", "1", regex=True).str.replace("2 asymtriques", "2").astype(int)
    res['presence_foil'] = res.presence_foil.apply(lambda x: True if x == 1 else False)
    res.hauteur_mat = res.hauteur_mat.str.replace("m| m|","", regex=True).str.replace(",",".").astype(float)
    res.surface_de_voiles_au_pres = res.surface_de_voiles_au_pres.str[0:3].astype(float)
    res.surface_de_voiles_au_portant = res.surface_de_voiles_au_portant.str[0:3].astype(float)
    res.voile_quille = res.voile_quille.apply(lambda s: unidecode.unidecode(s.lower()) if isinstance(s, str) else s).str.replace("basculante avec verin|basculante sur verin hydraulique", "verin", regex=True)
    res.date_de_lancement = pd.to_datetime(
        res.date_de_lancement.str.lower().apply(unidecode.unidecode).replace(mappers.mapper_month, regex=True), format="%d%m%Y"
    )
    res.chantier = res.chantier.replace(mappers.mapper_chantier, regex=False)
    res.architecte = res.architecte.replace(mappers.mapper_architecte, regex=False)
    
    # Cration de variable.
    res["voile_quille_acier"] = res.voile_quille.replace(mappers.mapper_voile_quille, regex=False).fillna(False)
    res["etendue"] = res.longueur * res.largeur
    res["race_start"] = datetime.datetime(2020,11,8)  #date de debut de course
    res["age"] = res.race_start - res.date_de_lancement
    res["age"] = res.age.dt.days

    # Telecharge les donnees sous forme d'excel si besoin
    res.to_excel("boat_features.xlsx")
    
    print("Done.")
    return res

def create_example_df(nb_points):
    """Create a random dataframe with 2 columns and nb_points rows."""
    latitude = np.random.random(nb_points)*100 + np.random.random(nb_points)*10
    longitude = np.random.random(nb_points)*100 + np.random.random(nb_points)*10
    df = pd.DataFrame(zip(latitude, longitude), columns = ["latitude", "longitude"])
    return df


def plot_boat_trajectory(list_of_dfs):
    """Plot trajectories. Each trajectory is a dataframe. A dataframe must have columns latitude and longitude"""
    # Set figure parameters.
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(18, 10))
    ax.set_aspect('equal')
   
    # Get world map and plot it.
    world = gpd.read_file(gpd.datasets.get_path('naturalearth_lowres'))
    world.plot(ax=ax)
   
    # Initialize set of colors.
    handles = []  # handles pour grer la lgende.
    my_colors = list(mcolors.BASE_COLORS.keys())
    my_colors.remove('w')  # Drop white (cannot be seen on map)
   
    # Get boat trajectory for each boat under right format.
    for df in list_of_dfs:
        nat_sail = df.nat_sail.iloc[0]
        # Get a color for the trajectory.
        i = random.randint(0, len(my_colors) - 1)
        color = my_colors.pop(i)
        handles.append(mpatches.Patch(color=color, label=nat_sail))
       
        # Plot the trajectory.
        geometry = [Point(xy) for xy in zip(df.longitude, df.latitude)]
        trajectory = GeoDataFrame(df, geometry=geometry)
        trajectory.plot(ax=ax, marker='o', color=color, markersize=8)
    
    # Creating legend with color box
    plt.legend(handles=handles, loc='upper left')
    plt.show();
    pass


def plot_boat_trajectory_interactive(list_of_dfs):
    """Plot trajectories. Each trajectory is a dataframe. A dataframe must have columns latitude and longitude"""
    # Get world map and plot it.
    m = folium.Map(max_bounds=True, min_zoom=2)
   
    # Initialize set of colors.
    colormap = cm.StepColormap(['green', 'orange',  'yellow', 'red'], vmin=0, vmax=4, index=[0, 1, 2, 3])
   
    # Get boat trajectory for each boat under right format.
    for i, df in enumerate (list_of_dfs):
        # Get a color for the trajectory.
        tooltip_text = ""
        nat_sail = df.nat_sail.iloc[0]
        skipper = df.skipper.iloc[0]
        for element in zip(df.latitude, df.longitude, df.date):
            coordinates = element[:2]
            date = element[2]
            tooltip = f" boat : {nat_sail} <br> skipper : {skipper} <br> date : {date.date()} <br> coordinates : {coordinates}"
            folium.CircleMarker(location=coordinates, radius=1.5, color=colormap(i+0.1), tooltip=tooltip).add_to(m)
   
    return m

x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(x, y, test_size = 0.2, random_state = random_state)

# Initializing the Random Forest Regression model with 12 decision trees.
model = RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators = 12, random_state = random_state)

# Fitting the Random Forest Regression model to the data
model.fit(x_train, y_train)

# Predicting the target values of the test set
y_pred = model.predict(x_test)

# RMSE (Root Mean Square Error)
rmse = float(format(np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred)), '.3f'))
print("RMSE: ", rmse)
print(f"L'erreur moyenne de prediction est de {rmse}, le modle prdit correctement la vitesse moyenne")
